.TH "devm_pinctrl_register" 9 "devm_pinctrl_register" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
devm_pinctrl_register \- Resource managed version of pinctrl_register().
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct pinctrl_dev *" devm_pinctrl_register
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "struct pinctrl_desc *pctldesc "  ","
.BI "void *driver_data "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
parent device for this pin controller
.IP "pctldesc" 12
descriptor for this pin controller
.IP "driver_data" 12
private pin controller data for this pin controller
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns an error pointer if pincontrol register failed. Otherwise
it returns valid pinctrl handle.

The pinctrl device will be automatically released when the device is unbound.
